---
import Layout from '../../_layout.astro';
import BackgroundEffect from '../../_BackgroundEffect.astro';
---

<Layout title="hx-get - Reference">
    {/* Page Header */}
    <header class="relative mb-16 border border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-800 rounded-xl overflow-hidden p-8 sm:p-10">
        <BackgroundEffect color="#a78bfa"/>

        <div class="relative z-10 flex flex-col gap-8">
            {/* Integrated Breadcrumbs Path */}
            <nav class="flex items-center gap-3">
                <a href="/preview/reference"
                   class="text-violet-600 dark:text-violet-400 font-bold text-xs uppercase tracking-widest interact:text-violet-800 transition-colors">
                    Reference
                </a>

                <span class="text-neutral-300 dark:text-neutral-700">/</span>

                <a href="/preview/reference/attributes"
                   class="text-sm font-medium text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-400 interact:text-neutral-900 dark:interact:text-neutral-200 transition-colors font-sans">
                    Attributes
                </a>

                <span class="text-neutral-300 dark:text-neutral-700">/</span>
            </nav>

            <h1 class="font-mono font-bold text-2xl sm:text-3xl text-neutral-900 dark:text-neutral-100 tracking-tight">
                hx-get
            </h1>
        </div>

        {/* Signature Block - Floating above */}
        <div class="relative z-10 w-full max-w-2xl border border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-800 rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-sm bg-white dark:bg-neutral-950 mt-10">
            <div class="flex items-center justify-between px-4 py-2.5 bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-900 border-b border-neutral-100 dark:border-neutral-800">
                <span class="font-sans text-xs font-bold text-neutral-500 dark:text-neutral-400 uppercase tracking-widest">
                    Signature
                </span>
                <div class="flex gap-1.5">
                    <div class="size-2.25 rounded-full bg-neutral-200 dark:bg-neutral-800"></div>
                    <div class="size-2.25 rounded-full bg-neutral-200 dark:bg-neutral-800"></div>
                    <div class="size-2.25 rounded-full bg-neutral-200 dark:bg-neutral-800"></div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="p-6 font-mono text-lg sm:text-xl leading-relaxed">
                <span class="text-violet-600 dark:text-violet-400 font-bold">hx-get</span><span
                    class="text-neutral-400 dark:text-neutral-600">=</span><span
                    class="text-emerald-600 dark:text-emerald-500">"</span><span
                    class="inline-block text-emerald-600 dark:text-emerald-500 font-medium transition-opacity duration-300 min-w-[12ch]"
                    id="sig-val"
                    _="on load
                         set examples to ['/users', '/search', '/settings', '/api/data']
                         set index to 0
                         put examples[0] into me
                         repeat forever
                           wait 2s
                           add .opacity-0
                           wait 300ms
                           set index to (index + 1) mod examples.length
                           put examples[index] into me
                           remove .opacity-0
                         end"
            >/users</span><span class="text-emerald-600 dark:text-emerald-500">"</span>
            </div>
        </div>
    </header>

    {/* Main Content (Prose) */}
    <div class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none prose-headings:font-chicago prose-h2:text-2xl prose-h2:mt-12 prose-h2:mb-6 prose-h2:border-b prose-h2:border-neutral-200 prose-h2:dark:border-neutral-800 prose-h2:pb-2">
        <p>
            The <code>hx-get</code> attribute will cause an element to issue a <code>GET</code> request to the specified
            URL and
            swap the HTML into the DOM using a swap strategy.
        </p>

        <p>
            Here is a simple example:
        </p>

        {/* Collapsible Code Block */}
        <div class="not-prose my-8 border border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-800 rounded-lg bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-950 overflow-hidden shadow-sm group/code open">
            {/* Header (Clickable) */}
            <button class="w-full flex items-center justify-between px-4 py-2.5 border-b border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-800 bg-neutral-100 dark:bg-neutral-900 hover:bg-neutral-200 dark:hover:bg-neutral-800/50 transition-colors cursor-pointer select-none"
                    _="on click toggle .open on closest .group/code then toggle .hidden on next <pre/>">

                <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
                    <i class="icon-[mdi--chevron-right] text-neutral-400 group-[.open]/code:rotate-90 transition-transform duration-200"></i>
                    <span class="text-xs font-bold text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 uppercase tracking-wider">
                        Example Code
                    </span>
                </div>

                <div class="flex gap-1.5 opacity-60 group-hover/code:opacity-100 transition-opacity">
                    <div class="size-2.25 rounded-full bg-neutral-200 dark:bg-neutral-800"></div>
                    <div class="size-2.25 rounded-full bg-neutral-200 dark:bg-neutral-800"></div>
                    <div class="size-2.25 rounded-full bg-neutral-200 dark:bg-neutral-800"></div>
                </div>
            </button>

            {/* Content */}
            <pre class="p-6 text-sm font-mono overflow-x-auto text-neutral-800 dark:text-neutral-200 bg-white dark:bg-neutral-950 border-t border-transparent"><code>&lt;<span
                    class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-350">div</span> <span
                    class="text-violet-600 dark:text-violet-400 font-bold">hx-get</span>=<span
                    class="text-emerald-600 dark:text-emerald-500">"/example"</span>&gt;
    Get Some HTML
&lt;/<span class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-350">div</span>&gt;</code></pre>
        </div>

        <p>
            This will issue a <code>GET</code> to <code>/example</code> and swap the returned HTML into the
            <code>div</code>.
        </p>

        <h2>Notes</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><code>hx-get</code> is the default behavior for <code>&lt;a&gt;</code> tags when using htmx, but can be
                explicit.
            </li>
            <li>By default, the request is triggered by the "natural" event of the element (click for buttons/links,
                change for inputs).
            </li>
            <li>You can modify the trigger using <a href="#">hx-trigger</a>.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</Layout>
